  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<h2></b>Description</b></h2></p><p>This +1 light mace is forged of black iron and topped with what appears to be a clenched fist with spikes protruding from between the fingers. As a move action, the wielder can expend 1 point from his arcane pool (as per a magusUM), 1 point from his arcane reservoir (as per an arcanistACG), or one use of fervor (as per a warpriestACG) to make a single melee attack with the signifer's fist. Characters without any of these options can instead activate a signifer's fist in this way as a standard action once per day. If the attack deals damage to a creature, the signifer's fist gains the bane weapon special ability against that creature's type (or subtype if the creature is a humanoid or outsider) for 1 minute. This benefit doesn't apply if the target is immune to bleed, though the attack still deals damage normally.<br><p><b>Base Item:</b> +1 light mace</p><h3><b>Requirements</b></h3><p>Craft Magic Arms and Armor, haste, summon monster I</p><h3><b>Source: </b></h3>Adventurer's Guide",
